              [36;1mMAP_SHARED [22;0mmappings ignore unknown flags in [31;3;1mflags[24;0m.  By contrast,
              when  creating  a  mapping using [36;1mMAP_SHARED_VALIDATE[22;0m, the kernel
              verifies all passed flags are known and fails the  mapping  with
              the  error  [36;1mEOPNOTSUPP  [22;0mfor unknown flags.  This mapping type is
              also required to be  able  to  use  some  mapping  flags  (e.g.,
              [36;1mMAP_SYNC[22;0m).

